@startuml
title Q&A and Word Cloud
hide footbox
autonumber

skinparam BackgroundColor transparent
skinparam SequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 20
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam MaxMessageSize 110
skinparam WrapWidth 220
skinparam RoundCorner 8

actor "Host browser" as Host
actor "Participant browser\nstatic/participant.js" as Participant
participant "Railway HTTP proxy" as RailwayHTTP
participant "Daemon QA router" as QAAPI
participant "Daemon wordcloud router" as WordcloudAPI
participant "Railway session WS" as RailwayWS
participant "Host local WS\nresolved names / scores" as HostWS

group Word cloud
Host -> WordcloudAPI: POST /host/wordcloud/topic
WordcloudAPI -> RailwayWS: broadcast wordcloud_updated(topic)

Participant -> RailwayHTTP: POST /api/participant/wordcloud/word
RailwayHTTP -> WordcloudAPI: proxy word submission
WordcloudAPI -> WordcloudAPI: require current_activity == wordcloud\nadd word\nadd 200 points
WordcloudAPI -> RailwayWS: write_back wordcloud_updated
WordcloudAPI -> RailwayWS: write_back scores_updated

opt Host clears the cloud or adds a seed word
  Host -> WordcloudAPI: POST /host/wordcloud/clear or /word
  WordcloudAPI -> RailwayWS: broadcast wordcloud_updated
end
end

group Q&A
Participant -> RailwayHTTP: POST /api/participant/qa/submit
RailwayHTTP -> QAAPI: proxy question submission
QAAPI -> QAAPI: save question\nadd 100 points to author
QAAPI -> RailwayWS: write_back qa_updated(raw questions)
QAAPI -> RailwayWS: write_back scores_updated
QAAPI -> HostWS: notify_host qa_updated(with names + avatars)
QAAPI -> HostWS: notify_host scores_updated

Participant -> RailwayHTTP: POST /api/participant/qa/upvote
RailwayHTTP -> QAAPI: proxy upvote request
QAAPI -> QAAPI: add upvote\nadd 50 points to author\nadd 25 points to voter
QAAPI -> RailwayWS: write_back qa_updated(raw questions)
QAAPI -> RailwayWS: write_back scores_updated
QAAPI -> HostWS: notify_host qa_updated(with names + avatars)
QAAPI -> HostWS: notify_host scores_updated

opt Host moderates the queue
  Host -> QAAPI: edit / delete / answered / clear
  QAAPI -> RailwayWS: broadcast qa_updated(raw questions)
  QAAPI -> HostWS: notify_host qa_updated(with names + avatars)
end
end

note over QAAPI, HostWS
Participants receive anonymous/raw question payloads.
The host gets a richer version with resolved participant names and avatars.
end note
@enduml
